medley

Class Note

  • java.lang.Object
    • medley.score.ScoreElement
      • medley.Note
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Element

    public class Note
extends ScoreElement
    Note class that contains all the informations about a musical note. This class represents a single note. A note is identified by a frequency and by a MIDI note number.

    A note has also a Name, represented using English literal notation an Accidental, that represent the alteration of a note, and an octave.

    A Note can be easily transposed using the methods semitoneUp, semitoneDown and transpose.

    Author:
    Salvatore Gentile
    See Also:
    Element, ScoreElement

        public Note(double frequency)
     throws IllegalArgumentException
        Initializes a newly created Note object with the specified frequency value.

        The new Note will be created using the value of the nearest valid note frequency.

        Parameters:

      • Note

        public Note(Note note)
        Initializes a newly created Note object with the same frequency value, MIDI note number, Tone and octave of the specified note. In other words, the newly created note is a copy of the argument note.

        The new Note has obviously the same Duration and volume value of the specified note.

        Parameters:
        note - a specified Note.

      • equals

        public boolean equals(Object o)
        Compares the specified object with this Note for equality.

        This implementation first checks if the specified object is a Note. If not, it returns false; if so, it checks if the specified object is this Note. If not, it returns false; if so, it compares the frequency of both notes.

        Overrides:
